// @run
// @log 8
// UFCS on an i32 receiver with a scalar argument: `(5).bump(3)` lowers to
// `bump(5, 3)`. Both operands are plain i32, so the rewritten vector is a pair
// of scalars — the simplest non-struct receiver shape, and the one that already
// worked through the emit-time fallback before the pre-collect rewrite covered it.
function bump(self: i32, by: i32): i32 { return self + by }
print((5).bump(3))
